##How to solve the travel difficulties of medical staff in Wuhan after the traffic shutdown

Micro Signal, Peopleweekly

Feature description, portrait of the Times.

Affected by the new traffic restrictions issued by Wuhan, but also out of concern for the owner's health, good luck team stopped picking up and sending medical staff. On the morning of the 26th, Wuhan residents offering free accommodation or delivering meals to doctors in some local mutual aid groups were still debating: Since we haven't received the notification yet, can we still pick up and drop off doctors on our own?

Medical staff cheer on each other in the intensive care isolation ward of Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University on Jan. 24. A battle is being waged against a new type of pneumonia, and medical workers are the retrograde party in the battle to prevent and control the disease

After the shutdown, citizens organized convoys of doctors to and from work

On January 25, the first day of the Lunar New Year, Xiao Xiong (not his real name) has not stopped ringing his mobile phone. Her mobile phone has nearly 30 local wechat groups in Wuhan, some responsible for docking supplies, some responsible for picking up and dropping off doctors and nurses, and some active in providing nearby accommodation for medical workers. Public transport in and around Wuhan was suspended on Tuesday as little bear and his friends organized a charity convoy to transport medical staff.

At one o'clock in the morning on New Year's Eve, little bear received a woman doctor in her forties. As soon as the doctor got into the car, he thanked her profusely, saying that he almost thought he would not be able to go home 18 or 9 kilometers away. After driving for a while, the doctor mentioned that the N95 mask was not enough. After seeing more than 100 patients a day, many colleagues had to walk home in the winter night. "I can't take it anymore, it's too much pressure, " the woman doctor burst into tears in the back seat.

A day later, the bear began to have a fever and cough. She was alert and immediately decided to rest at home, to isolate herself, not to go to the hospital to reduce the risk of cross-infection, and to continue to participate in the scheduling of the motorcade. She posted a message to her friends, warning them to keep out of contact.

Originally, Little Bear's 2020 Spring Festival was planned like this: a trip with her boyfriend, a trip to Disney world, a trip to a spa, and then an engagement ceremony. "This morning, he (boyfriend) told me that he would have helped me fulfill these wishes sooner, and he was so afraid that he would never see me again. "

Guo Xin, a private car owner who lives in Wuchang District, has joined the Wechat Group, which volunteers to pick up and drop off medical staff by district. On the 30th day of the New Year, he received two doctors, both on his way. When he picked up someone, he would take out an alcohol spray, leave the car on the side of the road for an hour, walk around on his own, and pick up the next one.

To reduce the risk of infection, Guo advised drivers not to carry patients and asked for identification or other means of identification. "The medical staff are all soldiers, we are the logistics, it's worth getting sick. "

But when he passed the four-lane residential area, saw a large number of people waiting at the gate of the residential area to take a taxi can not hit the heart is also sad, "it is not easy, " he said.

Late on the night of the 25th, little bear issued a notice, affected by the new traffic restrictions issued by Wuhan, but also out of concern for the owner's health, good luck team stopped picking up and sending medical staff. Wuhan from the 26th, the central urban area will implement vehicle control, traffic control departments will be prohibited vehicles through the text message 24 hours in advance to inform car owners. It is not clear which car owners will receive SMS notifications.

On the morning of the 26th, Wuhan residents offering free accommodation or delivering meals to doctors in some local mutual aid groups were still debating: Since we haven't received the notification yet, can we still pick up and drop off doctors on our own?

The troubled times of people with HIV and uremia

In recent three days, 14 cities in Hubei Province have implemented "city closure" measures, the road traffic disruption for the plight of life to be resolved.

Some supermarket workers walk an hour to work, while others walk three hours home from work.

Sudden changes may also bring unexpected crises to life. In a telephone interview, Zou Junxi (not his real name) kept crying. Returning home for the Spring Festival, he returned to a village in Tianmen, near Wuhan. He is HIV positive and needs to take his medicine on time every day. Because of the sudden road closure in the village, he was afraid that he would not be able to go to the Tianmen People's Hospital to get medicine. His meds are eight days away, but if they slip, HIV could mutate, and then he'll need to replace 3,000 of his monthly imports.

Worried, Zou junxi posted a request for help on his Weibo Account, and when a village worker came to his home to find out what was going on, he told his parents about his HIV status. His parents asked him why he had contracted the disease. He hid in his room and cried. He did not know how to answer his parents. He did not know whether the news would spread quickly in the village. "My parents may not be able to look up. " He also wanted to say to his parents, "let's eat together, let's live together. " It's not contagious.

Staff later came to his house to apologize. Tianmen City People's Hospital staff contacted him, but told him that the hospital can not adjust the way the drug, because every time HIV patients need to draw blood tests, must come in person. In coordination with the provincial centers for Disease Control and Prevention, HIV patients can receive a month's worth of medication at a local treatment site.

On the afternoon of the 25th, patients with uremia in the six hospitals in Wuhan were notified that they would no longer accept dialysis patients from next week because the six hospitals had been recruited as a new group of hospitals designated for the treatment of new coronary pneumonia.

The patient and his family are at a loss. Some have gone to other hospitals in the area, but at the moment Hankou's hospitals are stretched so thin that few have the capacity to receive dialysis patients. Because of the travel restriction, the patient's family worried about being unable to go to the hospital far away from home for dialysis.

The family worried to blame the doctor blame the nurse, hemodialysis room head nurse Chen Ming swear she is suddenly know the situation. She said, "I'm sorry! I'm sorry! But could you wait a minute and we'll run. "

She and other colleagues in the dialysis room went running and fought for it, telling everyone at 8 pm on the 25th: "(27) Monday is temporary (still available) dialysis, waiting for Referral Hospital! " After a while she said three times in the WECHAT group, "Dialysis, dialysis, dialysis. "

"Come Dialysis" these three words are like a spring rain. Half an hour later, the director of the dialysis unit told patients, "the director has got us a buffer period, and he's still working on it. We'll do everything we can to help. "

The patients thank and bless the doctors and nurses. There was tension, there was peace, and the doctor said, "we're still a family. "

An empty-cup hotel chain was booked by 69 medical staff, and the owner, Tao Lei, gave them a 10-day room card

More than 100 hotels in Wuhan offer free accommodation for doctors

We all know that everything will be fine, but this period of hardship is real, we have to bite the bullet.

Because of the public transport shutdown and long house calls, many doctors who live far away need to find accommodation closer to home. At present, more than 100 hotels in Wuhan offer free accommodation for the medical staff, hoping that during the days of the city's traffic shutdown, the medical staff fighting in the front line will have a place to rest nearby.

A support group summed up the hotel check-in notes

Detailed advice was written for both the medical staff and the hotel staff

Their contact groups often have such information, "Lung Hospital Staff Nine, did not go home for a few days to rest, is still in the hospital, hope that a nearby hotel can check in and rest as soon as possible. " Or, "medics at Wuchang Hospital, need lunch boxes. Who's got the resources? Thank you! "

At 3 p.m. on the first day of the Lunar New Year, the 25 rooms that had just been vacated at the Sindra apartment hotel were immediately filled by the night shift staff at Wuhan's Fourth Hospital. They bring their own bed sheets, bedclothes, toothbrushes, towels and other household items and disinfectant.

During the Spring Festival, the hotel only left a cleaning aunt. The paramedics offered to clean up, but the aunt refused. "after they leave, we'll sterilize ourselves, no problem, " said the woman, who bought bread and instant noodles at a nearby supermarket and prepared her own Three Meals a Day for the new year.

In Times of crisis, all departments must be on the front line. Zhang Xiao (not his real name) , a Otolaryngology at Wuhan's Third Hospital, has been on duty for 24 hours since 8 am on Wednesday. During the several-hour break, the department prepared instant noodles, milk and bread for her. She chose to stay close to the hospital, waiting to be informed and ready to take over. "when the chips are down, we need all the help we can get. "

It really helped the medical staff on the front lines. An Empty Cup hotel chain was booked by 69 medical staff, most of whom were from Wuhan Third People's Hospital. Boss Tao Lei gave them a ten-day room card, but also in the hotel lobby placed noodles, spices and simple induction cooker. Hotel disinfectant is enough, but the shortage of medical masks, Tao Lei bought 99 yuan 40 simple masks, his own car to the shop staff distribution, let them wear two at a time.

Medical Protective Masks in short supply, Tao Lei bought 99 yuan 40 simple masks, his own car to the shop staff, let them wear two at a time

Wuhan North Island Hotel apartment released information the same night, seven central South Hospital medical staff contact check-in. And Wuhan Kangaroo apartment at 12:00 PM on the 25th, 10 rooms are fully booked, eight of which were just on the night shift of the doctors to check in. KEIVIN APARTMENT & BED-AND-BREAKFAST 25,11 rooms will be arranged to the medical staff, to give them bed-and-breakfast Administrator Password, there is no specified check-out time.

Still, some shopkeepers expressed concern. The operator of the Hanfulin hotel is concerned that as an employer, private enterprises may not be able to bear the responsibility if hotel staff are infected as a result of receiving medical staff.

Most hotels are doing their best to take a series of precautions to avoid cross infection among health care workers and to ensure the health of hotel staff. Including store staff wearing masks and shower cap, check-out after disinfection, cleaning after bathing and so on.

The hotel has noodles, spices and a simple induction cooker in the lobby

State aid is beginning to arrive in Wuhan

For Xiao Xiong, the best news on the first day of the New Year is a picture she saw in her circle of friends: Several trucks hurtling across an empty bridge.

"The national relief supplies finally arrived in Wuhan and were ready to cry. You don't have to wear a mask all day, and you don't have to risk your life on the job. The front-line staff must protect themselves, and the people of Wuhan thank all the hospital workers who have come back to rescue during the New Year,"she wrote in a friend circle.

Starting from the 26th, Alibaba will provide 300 daily meals free of charge to Wuhan Red Cross Hospital and Wuhan Sixth Hospital, and 3,144 daily supplies of drinking water, instant noodles and self-heating food to 21 medical units in Wuchang District. TMALL supermarket and Hema fresh supermarket not closed, do not rise in prices, rolling on the shelf mask, disinfectant and other protective supplies. Hungry? No takeout, no delivery fee.

Although at 1:00 a.m. on the 26th, the medical team from Shanghai, shang was asking where he could buy three meals a day: "the doctor from Shanghai had brought his own supplies, but when he arrived at the local hospital, he couldn't even eat. ". The meeting is still going on, and tomorrow I will be stationed at the hospital in Hankou, where the disease is most serious, but I haven't even finished breakfast yet.

"That's the reality. We wait for things to get better, " said one.
